  <h1>Privacy Policy — Vision Simulator</h1>
  <div class="updated">Last updated: May 2026</div>

  <p>Vision Simulator is an educational tool created by Dr. Ryan Evans, OD. We respect your privacy. In short: <strong>the app collects nothing about you, and your camera images never leave your device.</strong></p>

  <h2>Camera Use</h2>
  <p>The app can use your device's camera so you can see how various vision conditions would affect a live view of your surroundings. The camera feed is processed <strong>entirely on your device, in real time</strong>. Camera images are never recorded, stored, or transmitted to us or to anyone else. Nothing from your camera leaves your device.</p>

  <h2>Photos You Upload</h2>
  <p>If you choose to upload a photo to apply an effect, that image is processed only on your device and is not uploaded to any server or retained after you close the app.</p>

  <h2>No Data Collection</h2>
  <p>Vision Simulator does not collect, store, or transmit any personal information. There are no accounts, no logins, and no tracking of any kind.</p>

  <h2>No Advertising or Analytics</h2>
  <p>The app contains no advertising, no analytics, and no third-party tracking software or SDKs.</p>

  <h2>Educational Use Only</h2>
  <p>This app is a visual demonstration for patient education. It is <strong>not a diagnostic tool</strong> and does not measure, diagnose, or treat any medical condition. It is not a substitute for a professional eye examination.</p>

  <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>Because the app collects no data whatsoever, it collects no data from children.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>If you have any questions about this privacy policy, please contact Dr. Ryan Evans, OD, through <a href="https://rjlcevans.com">rjlcevans.com</a>.</p>

